<TITLE> HC bars cop Mizan from district post </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 23 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Tuesday asked the government not to assign any district-level duty to Md Mizanur Rahman, who was removed from duty as Bagerhat police superintendent on an alleged bid to grab land. The bench of justices AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and Borhanuddin gave the order on a writ petition filed by rights organisation Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh. The court also asked the inspector general of police to make it know within 20 days what actions have been taken against him and whether any committee formed to probe the allegation. It gave the secretary and additional secretary of the home affairs ministry and the IGP three weeks to explain why punitive actions would not be taken against Mizan. The police officer was withdrawn from Bagerhat on Feb 20, as a number of newspapers reported that he was trying to grab land on the boundary of Bagerhat and Gopalganj districts. Police headquarters, however, did not give any reason for his withdrawal from Bagerhat
